sequenceDiagram
    participant Firm as Member Firm
    participant GW as Order Gateway
    participant Seq as Sequencer
    participant Log as Input Log
    participant ME as Matching Engine (per symbol)
    participant MD as Market Data Publisher

    Note over Firm,MD: ORDER ENTRY — pre-trade risk + sequence + match
    Firm->>GW: NewOrder (binary protocol)
    GW->>GW: auth + validate
    GW->>GW: pre-trade risk (limits, max size, kill switch)
    alt risk reject (fat finger / over limit)
        GW-XFirm: reject (does not enter log)
    else risk pass
        GW->>Seq: forward order
        Seq->>Seq: assign global sequence number
        Seq->>Log: persist before processing (durability)
        Log-->>Seq: durable
        Seq->>ME: dispatch to per-symbol engine

        Note over ME: single-threaded match loop (price-time priority)
        loop while qty>0 and best opposite price crosses
            ME->>ME: fill = min(qty, resting.qty)
            ME->>ME: create trade; decrement resting
            ME->>ME: pop resting if exhausted
        end
        alt residual remains
            ME->>ME: insert into book at price level
        end

        ME-)MD: ExecutionReport(s) + TradeReport(s)
        ME-)Firm: ack via gateway path
        MD-)Firm: multicast trade + book updates
    end

    Note over Log,ME: HOT STANDBY replays same log in lockstep — promotes on primary failure
